<i>♪ In Foam Town</i>

05:44.468 --> 05:46.268
<i>♪ Yeah</i>

05:47.738 --> 05:49.572
<i>♪ There's no bruises</i>
<i>or concussions</i>

05:49.574 --> 05:50.972
<i>♪ There's no painful</i>
<i>repercussions</i>

05:50.974 --> 05:55.044
<i>♪ There's no braces</i>
<i>There's no bandages</i>
<i>No hospital stay</i>

05:55.146 --> 05:56.479
<i>♪ If you jump</i>
<i>and try to land it</i>

05:56.481 --> 05:57.779
<i>♪ You can eat it</i>
<i>or face-plant it</i>

05:57.781 --> 06:02.752
<i>♪ And you know</i>
<i>that your insurance plan</i>
<i>will not have to pay</i>

06:02.754 --> 06:05.621
♪ Come on down to Foam Town

06:05.822 --> 06:07.657
♪ Come on down to Foam Town

06:07.858 --> 06:09.625
<i>♪ Come on down</i>

06:09.627 --> 06:11.394
<i>♪ Just come on down</i>
<i>to Foam Town</i>

06:11.396 --> 06:14.730
♪ Come on down to Foam Town

06:14.732 --> 06:16.599
<i>♪ Yeah! Come on down</i>

06:16.833 --> 06:18.801
<i>♪ Come on down to Foam Town</i>

06:19.569 --> 06:22.805
And over here
are the models of our
robotically operated rovers.

06:22.807 --> 06:24.240
The Mars rover,

06:24.242 --> 06:25.341
the Moon rover,

06:25.343 --> 06:26.676
and this is the Irish rover.

06:26.678 --> 06:28.744
You sent a rover
to Ireland?

06:28.746 --> 06:30.446
Well, we had to
test it somewhere.

06:30.448 --> 06:34.183
♪ In a land afar in Castlebar
Many months ago

06:34.651 --> 06:37.653
<i>♪ We sent an Irish rover</i>
<i>To look around, you know</i>

06:38.288 --> 06:40.256
<i>♪ With a tur-la-lur-la</i>
<i>Fiddle-die-dee</i>

06:40.258 --> 06:41.824
<i>♪ And a tur-a-fiddle-die-do</i>

06:41.826 --> 06:45.394
♪ In a land afar in Castlebar
Many months ago ♪

06:49.966 --> 06:51.165
It took a couple of months,

06:51.167 --> 06:54.537
but we're finally
starting to get some
really great pictures back.

06:54.971 --> 06:56.806
Thank you for the blanket,
Perry the Platypus.

06:56.808 --> 06:58.340
VANESSA: Dad?
Vanessa?

06:58.342 --> 07:00.443
(WHISPERING)
Oh, no! Vanessa,
get out of there!

07:00.445 --> 07:02.478
There's a huge bat
on the loose.

07:02.480 --> 07:03.579
Really?

07:03.581 --> 07:04.914
(SHRIEKING)

07:04.916 --> 07:06.382
VANESSA: Wow! Cool.

07:06.384 --> 07:08.417
It looks like
your cousin, Narthelliot.

07:08.419 --> 07:11.220
(QUIETLY)
No sudden movements
or loud noises, Vanessa.

07:11.222 --> 07:14.590
Dad, relax. It's just a bat.
They just eat bugs.

07:14.592 --> 07:15.925
But it's a very big bat!

07:15.927 --> 07:18.527
Now, come on.
Just, just stand up.
It's okay.

07:18.529 --> 07:19.929
It's time to face
your fear.
(BAT GROWLING)

07:19.931 --> 07:21.263
(NERVOUSLY)
Well, okay...

07:21.265 --> 07:22.398
(MUFFLED GROANING)

07:22.400 --> 07:25.034
Oh, no, no! Bad bat!
Spit him out!

07:25.836 --> 07:26.969
(GROANS)

07:27.537 --> 07:29.472
Gross!
(SCREAMS)

07:30.440 --> 07:31.941
Oh, yeah, this is much better!
(BAT SHRIEKING)

07:31.943 --> 07:33.008
Dad!

07:33.610 --> 07:34.609
Oh, hey, Perry.

07:34.611 --> 07:37.813
I was wondering
if you could help me.
(ENGINE FIRING UP)

07:37.815 --> 07:40.282
Thanks, Perry.
You're a peach.

07:40.284 --> 07:41.817
So, what did I miss?

07:41.819 --> 07:44.687
Oh, hey, Narthelliot!
We were just talking
about you.

07:44.689 --> 07:47.857
JACK: Of course,
even better than using
a rover, we have these.

07:47.859 --> 07:49.925
We call them global
surveillance satellites.

07:49.927 --> 07:51.894
No matter where you are
on this Earth,

07:51.896 --> 07:54.296
there's always one of these
flying above you in orbit,

07:54.298 --> 07:55.898
streaming live video
to us here.

07:55.900 --> 07:58.768
That's right.
Here's the outside
of our building, right now.

07:58.770 --> 08:00.903
And we can look up
any location, instantly.

08:00.905 --> 08:03.272
The Eiffel Tower,
the Taj Mahal...

08:03.274 --> 08:05.741
So, you could look down
on anybody's backyard

08:05.743 --> 08:07.041
and just see
what they're doing?

08:07.043 --> 08:09.879
Pretty cool, huh?
Wow, that's got to be
handy for something.

08:09.881 --> 08:11.547
And three.

08:11.549 --> 08:13.916
Two. One...

08:14.785 --> 08:17.019
What?
Really?
All right.

08:17.021 --> 08:18.888
(SHRIEKING)

08:18.890 --> 08:21.390
(DOOFENSHMIRTZ SCREAMING)

08:21.392 --> 08:24.059
Whoa! Oh, I get it.
This is what it does.

08:24.061 --> 08:25.528
Flying through a hoop.

08:25.530 --> 08:26.929
That's what I get...

08:26.931 --> 08:28.464
For buying a bat...

08:28.466 --> 08:29.999
From a defunct...

08:30.001 --> 08:31.400
Bat circus!

08:31.568 --> 08:32.835
So, having fun yet?

08:32.969 --> 08:33.968
Oh, you know I am!

08:33.970 --> 08:36.672
You know, my dad
goes on and on
about the cafeteria here,

08:36.674 --> 08:38.808
and I think he's right.
This food is...
(SPITTING)

08:38.810 --> 08:39.808
(GASPS)
I've got an idea!

08:39.810 --> 08:43.946
My brothers are probably
building something
in our backyard right now,

08:43.948 --> 08:47.016
and we can use
the surveillance satellite
to catch them doing it!

08:47.018 --> 08:47.916
Come on!

08:47.918 --> 08:50.085
I was wondering
how long that would take.

08:51.688 --> 08:53.656
Just let me punch in
my address...

08:54.090 --> 08:56.959
(GASPS) Oh, my gosh!
I knew it! Look at that thing!

08:56.961 --> 08:58.394
Wow. What is it?

08:58.396 --> 09:00.629
It's an eye in the sky bust!

09:00.631 --> 09:02.331
Come on,
let's go get my mom.

09:02.333 --> 09:05.067
Okay, Ferb, turn it off.
Let's take a little break.

09:07.003 --> 09:09.438
(BUFORD GRUNTING)

09:09.706 --> 09:10.705
You okay, Buford?

09:10.707 --> 09:13.509
I'm having
the time of my life!
Is anybody else hungry?

09:13.511 --> 09:15.678
I am!
Come on, let's go see
what's in the kitchen.

09:19.950 --> 09:21.450
DOOFENSHMIRTZ: Oh no!
Oh, no, no! Not again!

09:21.452 --> 09:24.119
(CLANGING)
Ow, my head!
Ow, my head again!

09:24.721 --> 09:26.589
Ow! Now I forgot math.

09:26.790 --> 09:28.691
Ow! There goes Social Studies.

09:29.059 --> 09:29.992
Oh, good! They're back!

09:31.061 --> 09:32.661
This way, Mom.

09:32.663 --> 09:33.829
Just see for yourself.

09:33.997 --> 09:37.032
Oh, wow! It's our house.

09:37.034 --> 09:38.367
And you can see the boys!

09:38.369 --> 09:40.002
And their
little skateboards.

09:40.437 --> 09:41.670
Hi, boys!

09:41.672 --> 09:43.873
They can't hear you,
you know.
I know.

09:43.875 --> 09:45.774
Hi! Whoo-hoo!

09:46.009 --> 09:47.843
Hey! Foam Town's gone.

09:47.845 --> 09:50.446
You say that like
it doesn't happen every day.

09:50.448 --> 09:53.015
And you say that
like an angry old prospector.

09:53.017 --> 09:54.483
What does that
even mean?

09:54.485 --> 09:56.118
I stand by that metaphor.

09:56.120 --> 09:58.020
Finally, Daisy,
we're here.

09:58.022 --> 10:02.024
Our new home!
Lots of elbow-room
and no one to bother us.

10:02.026 --> 10:06.128
The last frontier!
A place where a man
and his donkey can...

10:06.863 --> 10:07.862
Dang it!

10:07.864 --> 10:10.833
Come on, Daisy,
we're heading west.

10:10.967 --> 10:13.035
(DOOFENSHMIRTZ SCREAMING)

10:13.037 --> 10:15.137
Perry the Platypus!
Welcome to Saint Louis.

10:15.139 --> 10:17.907
Now, do something
about this bat, please!

10:19.075 --> 10:19.974
(SQUEAKING)

10:19.976 --> 10:22.878
(YELPS)
Well, at least I lost
my fear of bats.

10:22.880 --> 10:24.113
(CRASHING)
(GRUNTS)

10:24.115 --> 10:25.313
WAITRESS: Oh, it's you again.

10:25.315 --> 10:26.916
DOOFENSHMIRTZ: (SCREAMING)
Go away, go away, go away!

10:26.918 --> 10:29.118
WAITRESS: Oh,
just stop it.

10:31.588 --> 10:34.590
<i>♪ There's nothing</i>
<i>that I've found as good</i>
<i>as goin' round and round</i>

10:34.592 --> 10:35.658
<i>♪ In Foam Town</i>

10:36.559 --> 10:38.027
<i>♪ In Foam Town</i>

10:38.528 --> 10:39.895
♪ I used to skin my knees
(WHOOPING)

10:39.897 --> 10:42.865
<i>♪ But here it doesn't</i>
<i>matter where I fall</i>

10:45.635 --> 10:48.704
♪ You'll never get scarred
'cause nothing's really hard

10:48.706 --> 10:50.105
♪ In Foam Town

10:52.609 --> 10:58.847
♪ So take a rollin' ride
